{
  "text": "This study shows that cyclic stretch of NRAM results in (1) activation of immediate early genes, distinct signalling pathways, changes related to hypertrophy and dedifferentiation, elevation of stress markers, electrical remodelling and cell death; [CITATION_1] signalling, but not of CaMKII signalling; (3) inhibition of skeletal aactin expression with pravastatin and (4) the demonstration that BNP in atrial cells is a stronger stress marker than ANP in neonatal atrial cardiomyocytes in vitro.",
